<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900717-0129</DOCNO><DOCID>900717-0129.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Borland International Inc.:   Software Concern Reports   Net Surged in Its 1st Period</HL><DATE>07/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BORL</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Borland International Inc. reported unexpectedly strongincreases in fiscal first-quarter profit and revenue.   The Scotts Valley, Calif., computer software company saidprofit nearly tripled to $4.6 million, or 32 cents a share,in the quarter ended June 30, compared with $1.6 million, or13 cents, a year earlier. Analysts had expected Borland toearn between 23 cents and 28 cents a share. The company citedincreased sales of its Paradox database, Quattro Prospreadsheet and Turbo C++ programming language.</LP><TEXT>   Borland said revenue increased 78% to $41.1 million from$23 million a year earlier. The results were released aftermarkets closed. In national over-the-counter trading, Borlandclosed up 75 cents at $18.875.</TEXT></DOC>